  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Do I really need to buy tires in pairs?",
  "response": "When considering whether to replace tires in pairs or individually, several factors come into play to ensure safety, performance, and vehicle integrity:\n\n1. **General Recommendation: Replace in Pairs**  \n   - **Same Axle Replacement**: For optimal traction and handling, tires on the same axle (front or rear) should have matching tread depth, type, and size. Mismatched tires can lead to uneven wear, poor handling, or instability, especially in wet or slippery conditions.  \n   - **Safety**: Newer tires on the rear axle improve stability and reduce the risk of oversteer (for front-wheel-drive vehicles) or understeer (for rear-wheel-drive vehicles).\n\n2. **Exceptions for Single Tire Replacement**  \n   - **Minor Tread Difference**: If the remaining tires are nearly new (e.g., <5,000 miles), replacing just one tire *may* be acceptable, provided it **exactly matches** the brand, model, size, and tread pattern of the others.  \n   - **Tread Depth Tolerance**: Ensure the new tire\u2019s tread depth is within **2/32 of an inch** of the others. Exceeding this may strain drivetrain components.\n\n3. **All-Wheel/4-Wheel Drive (AWD/4WD) Vehicles**  \n   - **Strict Tread Requirements**: Manufacturers often mandate all four tires have uniform tread depth (typically within **2/32\u20133/32 of an inch**). Replacing a single tire risks drivetrain damage. Solutions include:  \n     - Replacing all four tires.  \n     - Shaving the new tire to match existing tread depth (a specialized service).  \n\n4. **When to Replace All Four**  \n   - If tires are significantly worn or aged (even if only one is damaged), full replacement ensures balanced performance.  \n   - Critical for AWD/4WD systems to avoid mechanical stress.\n\n**Practical Advice**:  \n- **Front-Wheel/ Rear-Wheel Drive**: Replace pairs on the same axle, prioritizing new tires on the rear for stability.  \n- **AWD/4WD**: Consult your manual; full replacement is often safest.  \n- **Mismatched Tires**: Avoid mixing brands/models, as this can compromise handling and safety.\n\nIn short, while replacing pairs is ideal, single replacements are possible under strict conditions. Always prioritize uniformity in tread and consult a professional for guidance tailored to your vehicle.",
